RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 84. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRINCE PRANCEALOT hustled clear early, showed the way two wide through the turn and drew off in the final furlong under a drive. CURLIN'S KAOS broke in and bumped, chased outside a rival up the backstretch, rounded the bend four wide, finished willingly through the lane, failed to make any headway on the winner late but stayed on to secure the place. FINAL STORM got bumped on both sides at the start, chased the lone leader three wide through the turn and lacked a bid. TRAVELIN' SHOW off slow to begin, chased four wide into the turn, five wide into the stretch and could not threaten. MR. CHIVAS took a bump from outside at the start, tracked along the rail into and around the bend, asked in the lane but weakened in the late stages. BILLY JOE SHAVER chased three wide into the turn, moved out around the bend and came five wide into the stretch and could not respond when called upon. RUNNING TIGER broke a step slow from outside, raced off the pace outside a rival early on, rounded the bend four, five then six wide and was not a factor. DUE TO A TIMER MALFUNCTION THE FIRST RACE WAS HAND-TIMED.

ENTRY.NAME: Mr. Chivas
ENTRY.OWNER: Knapp Steve R Lovingier Terry C Miller Martha and Moroney John

ENTRY.NAME: Final Storm
ENTRY.OWNER: Jett T Lawrence and Jett Ann
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped both sides, chased 3wide, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Curlin's Kaos
ENTRY.OWNER: Zephyr Racing LLC and Pais Alfred

ENTRY.NAME: Running Tiger
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, 4-6wide, drifted in stretch, no factor

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 75. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAGNIFICENT RIDE dueled for command outside KING ZOG, inched ahead on the turn, raced on even terms again into the final furlong, drifted inward and drew clear to prove best. KING ZOG dueled for the lead from inside, kept the pressure on through the turn, headed the leader again at the eighth pole, drifted toward the inside and yielded late. BLUEGRASS RYDER chased three wide into the turn, moved into the two path, angled out and came five wide into the stretch and lacked a bid. GETEMDUSTY broke a step slow, tracked outside a rival, went four wide into the turn, six wide into the lane and weakened. ATTA BOY LLOYD broke a step slow then got crowded and took up early, chased three to four wide on the turn and weakened. NAHAN chased widest up the backstretch, five wide into the turn, angled down the rail around the bend and came up empty. DUE TO A TIMER MALFUNCTION THE FIRST QUARTER FRACTION WAS HAND-TIMED.

ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled inside, drifted in, yielded late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since October 8 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLESSED ANGEL sprinted clear from outside, showed the way three wide through the turn, asked right handed at the three-sixteenths pole, switched to the left hand midstretch while increasing the lead, went back to the right hand approaching deep stretch and held safely. BACK ON THE STREET brushed the gate to come away a hair slow, coaxed to a forward position outside a pair of rivals, chased four wide into the lane, kept on through the final furlong and bested the others while whittling the gap on the winner late. LA PALOMA BLANCA had to steady when running up on the heels of BLESSED ANGEL early, chased two wide outside a rival into and around the turn, moved out in the stretch and lacked a bid. SUGAR SUGAR broke well then was taken to the back, trailed three wide into the lane, angled out in upper stretch and could not rally. MODERA chased along the inside into the turn, lost ground around the bend, moved out in upper stretch and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Modera
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, moved out upper, tired

ENTRY.NAME: La Paloma Blanca
ENTRY.OWNER: Altamira Racing Stable Barber Gary and Nentwig Michael

ENTRY.NAME: Back On the Street
ENTRY.OWNER: JCB Group Dang Randy Enterante Frank Kawaguchi Ken and Londo Christine

ENTRY.NAME: Sugar Sugar
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, taken back, 3wide, angled out upper, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 81. Maiden Claiming Purse 29000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EL REY DORADO took control early, moved out and showed the way off the rail up the backstretch, rounded the bend three to four wide, flagged with the whip in the lane, asked right handed past the eighth pole and stayed clear to the wire. DARK MARCUS chased five wide around the bend, stayed within striking distance into the final furlong but finished evenly late. BIG DRINKER got bumped and crowded leaving the gate, trailed on the inside into the turn, tipped two wide leaving the bend and produced a mild rally to earn the show honors. HILL SIXTEEN got forced into inner rival at the start, raced up close outside the leader to the turn, chased four to five wide on the bend, then weakened in the final furlong. RAYS REGAL came in and bothered inner rivals at the start, tracked two wide then along the rail on the turn and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Big Drinker
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped back start, inside-2wide, mild rally

ENTRY.NAME: Hill Sixteen
ENTRY.OWNER: Altamira Racing Stable CYBT Nentwig Michael and Weiner Daniel
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced in/bumped start, up close outside, chased 4-5wide,weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 5F Dirt CR: 83. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(Any Race at Five Furlongs or Less Not Considered).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AFTERNOON HEAT away quickly from outside, chased four deep into the turn, spun five wide into the lane, rallied from outside and drove past inner rivals approaching the wire. CROSSKIRK chased three deep into the turn, exited the bend four wide, rallied through the lane, challenged in the final sixteenth but was outclosed by AFTERNOON HEAT in the final moments. EQUIPO A pressed the pace from outside, kept the pressure on three wide through the turn, took over in upper stretch, put away inner rival past the eight pole but was run down by the outer pair late. SAN JAC chased four wide into the turn, moved into the three path around the bend and summoned a mild response to earn a minor award. KING ADROCK set the pace inside a rival up the backstretch, maintained a short lead two wide around the bend, relinquished the lead in upper stretch, fought back into the final furlong, then weakened late. WARRENS WORLD broke a step slow, got crowded early, raced near the back three then four wide on the turn, churned on through the lane but failed to threaten. DIVINE FEMININE brushed and put in tight between early, saved ground at the back around the bend, steered out in the lane and improved position. AGRIGENTO brushed with outer rival early, chased in the two path outside a rival and failed to respond to urging. MIGHTY MATT chased wide up the backstretch off the pace, rounded the bend five then six wide and failed to menace. KISLOVODSK chased along the rail to upper stretch and weakened down after.

ENTRY.OWNER: Jimmy Rex Robinson Family Trust Exelby Randy and Mayo Tom

ENTRY.NAME: Divine Feminine
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed/tight early, saved ground, angled out str, improved

ENTRY.NAME: King Adrock
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace 2path, dueled, weakened late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 5F Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THRUST pressed the pace from outside, fought three wide around the bend, shook free in upper stretch and was kept to task to the wire. SMARTY NOSE chased along the inside into the turn, angled out to the four path around the bend, rallied and overtook BEYOND COMPARE late for the place. BEYOND COMPARE hustled to the front, set the pace inside THRUST into the turn, battled in the two path around the bend, could not keep up with that rival in upper stretch and was outfinished for second in deep stretch. NUMBER ONE SON broke a step slow and had his path taken at the start, trailed two wide into the lane, moved out and failed to menace while earning a minor award. CAPACITY tracked off the pace on the inside, saved ground through the turn and was not a factor. CHASING ALCHEMY stalked off the inside to the turn, rounded the bend four then three wide and weakened. WON BID stumbled and broke inward, forwardly placed early inside rivals, cut the corner into the lane and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Number One Son
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost path start, 2wide, moved out, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Thrust
ENTRY.OWNER: Nguyen Calvin and Tran Joey C
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed outside, dueled, cleared upper, kept to task

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: T & G Farm of Ketnucky, LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 29000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 8 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TANGLEDUPINGREY prompted the pace from inside, moved up on even terms on the turn, shook free midstretch and drew away. SOUL OF MIDNIGHT took control early and set the pace outside TANGLEDUPINGREY early, dueled with that rival while in the three path on the turn, failed to kick on with that rival midstretch and stayed on to hold the place. TAKE ACTION tracked four wide into the turn, exited the bend five wide and was along for the show. PAPA TIGER chased three then four wide on the turn and weakened. ROAD OF LOVE trailed five wide into the turn, angled down to the three path around the bend and lacked a rally. EAGLES LANDING raced in range off the rail, rounded the bend two then three wide and weakened down the lane. MACNAMARA off slow in the beginning, chased on the inside through the turn and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Tangledupingrey
ENTRY.OWNER: Han Moon S and Medina Lizbeth

ENTRY.NAME: Take Action
ENTRY.OWNER: Bass II Perry R and Bass Ramona S

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 85. Claiming Purse 25000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(Any Race at Five Furlongs or Less Not Considered ).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHOA BUDDY traveled near the back early on, rounded the bend two to three wide, steered out in the lane, rallied to within striking distance with a sixteenth remaining and got up at the wire. DIVINE RASCAL dueled for the lead from outside, three wide around the turn, battled to the eighth pole, put away I'M A LUCKY MAN past the eighth pole, led clear into deep stretch and got nailed at the wire. BRUTTO stalked from inside into the turn, asked right handed around the bend, cut the corner into the stretch and gained the show. TOP OF MY GAME chased outside a rival towards the rear then trailed leaving the backstretch, saved ground around the bend, angled out in upper stretch, rounded out the superfecta but could not threaten for the top placings. I'M A LUCKY MAN dueled for command inside DIVINE RASCAL up the backstretch, fought two wide around the bend, stayed on to the eighth pole, then weakened in the late stages. MISSED CALL dropped back early, navigated the turn three then four wide and failed to menace. TOM BOMBADIL stalked three wide into the turn, exited the bend four wide and weakened.
